Currently the _unary_ `assertNull` method is defined as,

    static public void assertNull(Object object) {
        assertNull(null, object);
    }

    static public void assertNull(String message, Object object) {
        assertTrue(message, object == null);
    }

This means that, upon failure, all we know is that `object` was not actually `null`. It would be nice if `assertNull` would report the actual value in the exception it throws, just like `assertEquals` and `assertSame`.

